<title>ITALY: CYCLING-TONKOV WINS 21ST GIRO STAGE.</title>
<headline>CYCLING-TONKOV WINS 21ST GIRO STAGE.</headline>
<dateline>EDOLO, Italy 1997-06-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>Pavel Tonkov of Russia won the 238-km 21st stage of the Giro d'Italia cycle race on Saturday, according to provisional results.  </p>
<p>Italy's Ivan Gotti was second and his compatriot Wladimir Belli was third, also provisional.</p>
<p>Gotti retained the overall lead.</p>
